  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. The area of a square is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s squared\"><msup><mi>s</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\"><mi>s</mi></math> is the length of each side of the square. It's given that the length of each side of a square is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"94 cm\"><mn>94</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>. It follows that the area, in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"cm Superscript 2\"><msup><mtext>cm</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, of the square is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis 94 right parenthesis squared\"><msup><mfenced><mn>94</mn></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"94 dot 94\"><mn>94</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>94</mn></math>. Therefore, the expression that gives the area, in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"cm Superscript 2\"><msup><mtext>cm</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, of the square is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"94 dot 94\"><mn>94</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>94</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>\n<p>Choice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>\n<p>Choice C is incorrect. This expression gives the perimeter, in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"cm\"><mtext>cm</mtext></math>,&nbsp;of the square.</p>",
